node.description: I was hired on by Getter in the early stages of this project to collaborate with Planesâ€”a London-based digital agency. Together, our Getter Dev team worked together to design and develop a web app for Getter, an on-demand tool and construction supply delivery service operating in Australia. The overarching goal of this project is to scale, grow, and optimize existing business and technological processes to transform Getter into the go-to on-demand trade supplier in Australasia.

node.description: In the first half of 2020, I stumbled across Koji, a web platform that focused on providing a space for developers like myself to develop templates for users to create customizable apps and games with little to no code experience required. Side Mine/Pirate's Plunder is the most extensive of the templates I created.
node.overview: Pirate's Plunder is a match-three browser game built with Phaser 3, a JavaScript game development framework.
